      "body" : "I came here because I believed parameters of type <code>-Dname=value</code> are JVM arguments and that there is no intrinsic difference to <code>-X</code> arguments. Actually, they are both passed to java and not the application at the command line and as evidence by example, in maven you can pass both as <code>-Drun.jvmArguments=...</code>. I believe that is why it is upvoted."
